# Start of question: potential surfaces and electric field between parallel plates
:TYPE:MC:1:0:C
:TITLE:potential surfaces and electric field between parallel plates
:FEEDBACK:H

:QUESTION:H
Two parallel plates are connected to a battery so that one is at a potential 1.5 V higher than the other.  The equipotential surfaces and electric field lines are best described by\:
:IMAGE:
:LAYOUT:vertical
:ANSWERORDER:randomized
:INDICES:letters
:ANSWER1:100:H
the equipotential surfaces are parallel to the plates and the electric field lines are perpendicular the equipotential surfaces pointing from the higher potential plate to the lower potential plate.
:ANSWER2:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are parallel to the plates and the electric field lines are perpendicular the equipotential surfaces pointing from the lower potential plate to the higher potential plate.
:ANSWER3:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are perpendicular to the plates and the electrical field lines are parallel to the equipotential surfaces pointing from the higher potential plate to the lower potential plate.
:ANSWER4:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are perpendicular to the plates and the electrical field lines are parallel to the equipotential surfaces pointing from the lower potential plate to the higher potential plate.
:ANSWER5:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are perpendicular to the plates and the electrical field lines are parallel to the plates.
:CAT:electric potential
:Used By1:3088324804,3183399696
:Used By3:3183399696,3088324804
# End of question: potential surfaces and electric field between parallel plates

