# Start of question: equipotential surfaces and electrical field lines around a positive charge
:TYPE:MC:1:0:C
:TITLE:equipotential surfaces and electrical field lines around a positive charge
:FEEDBACK:H

:QUESTION:H
A small conducting sphere has a positive net charge.  No other charged objects are nearby.  The equipotential surfaces and electrical field lines around the sphere are best described by
:IMAGE:
:LAYOUT:vertical
:ANSWERORDER:randomized
:INDICES:letters
:ANSWER1:100:H
the equipotential surfaces are spheres centered on the charged sphere and the electrical field lines point directly away from the charged sphere.
:ANSWER2:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are spheres centered on the charged sphere and the electrical field lines point directly towards the charged sphere.
:ANSWER3:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are spheres centered on the charged sphere and the electrical field lines loop from one side of the sphere around to the other.
:ANSWER4:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are parallel planes and the electrical field lines point directly away from the charged sphere.
:ANSWER5:0:H
the equipotential surfaces are parallel planes and the electrical field lines point directly towards the charged sphere.
:CAT:electric potential
:Used By1:3088324804,3183399696
:Used By3:3183399696,3088324804
# End of question: equipotential surfaces and electrical field lines around a positive charge

